blog.name: depressingphangirl04
blog.title: Megan Xx
blog.description: interavtice introverts ~ 15/05/18

title: Dear Dan & Phil...
body:
Even though Dan & Phil will probably never see this, I wanted to share my story with fellow people of the internet. This was literally the best day of my life. The day I discovered these two Internet Cult Leaders was the day where I would have something to look forward to. It was an incredible world and I don’t know where I would be without it. Dan & Phil always had a way to make my life a whole lot better. I was never a happy kid/teenager so it was great to have someone who was there for me 24/7 in the form of videos. Phil’s videos never failed to make me smile after a hard day. Dan’s video for Mental Health Awareness encouraged me to talk to someone about my problems and I could never have done it without him. In their own way, they both helped me a whole lot and I hope they realise by just doing what they do everyday, somewhere out there, I can guarantee they are helping someone whether its in a small way or a big way. What I’m trying to say is they have a massive impact on so many people’s lives in such a good way and the world is so lucky to have  such amazing people. They don’t deserve all the hate they get. They are both such kind people and try to avoid drama in their careers and in their Phandom. They have done things for charities and are just generally good people. I know that some people say they get payed for doing nothing, but people forget how much time and effort goes into making YouTube content. There’s all of the planning, writing, actual filming, editing and uploading which can take days at a time. They don’t just do YouTube though. Dan & Phil worked at BBC and had a radio show once a week, they’ve been on 2 world tours, released 2 books and won so many awards. I just think that there is no way to repay Dan and Phil for what they’ve done for me personally and I’m sure other members of the Phandom can agree with me. So if Dan or Phil see this, I just want to say Thank You. Please don’t ever stop being yourself because I just know that you are helping so many people. The week before I went to Interactive Introverts, I was having a really tough time and your show made me smile non-stop for hours and now, months later, a day doesn’t go by without me thinking about that day and smiling, wanting to replay that day and find some way to show how grateful I am. So just..Thank You So Much. I love you guys!!

~Megan Xx <3
